          <avActivityHighlights>In these regions the avalanche danger is high (level 4).</avActivityHighlights>
          <avActivityComment>Heavy snowfall. The wind will be moderate to strong. &lt;br/&gt; The snowpack remains in most cases unstable. Natural avalanches are possible over a wide area. Avalanches can penetrate deep layers reach very large size. &lt;br/&gt; Without question, it is inadvisable to engage in backcountry touring.</avActivityComment>
          <snowpackStructureComment>Somewhat older wind slabs remain for the foreseeable future prone to triggering. As a consequence of new snow and wind, further wind slabs will form. &lt;br/&gt; Numerous weak layers exist in the old snowpack in particular on shady slopes.</snowpackStructureComment>
          <tendencyComment>Light snowfall.</tendencyComment>
